# ⏳ Multi Countdown Timer Web App

A beautifully designed, fully responsive countdown timer web application built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to set multiple countdown timers, manage them with ease, and get alerted with an audio notification when a timer ends. This app is perfect for events, study sessions, reminders, or daily routines.

## 🌟 Features

- ✅ Create unlimited countdown timers
- 📝 Name each timer for better organization
- 📅 Select exact date and time for each timer
- ⏸ Pause/Resume individual timers
- ❌ Cancel timers anytime
- 🔔 Audible alarm when a timer completes
- 📱 Fully responsive for mobile, tablet, and desktop
- 🎨 Clean UI with animated timer cards and styled buttons
- 🌈 Gradient background with modern design

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

This project is developed using:

- 🧱 HTML5 – semantic structure
- 🎨 CSS3 – styling with Flexbox & media queries
- ⚙️ JavaScript (ES6+) – timer logic and DOM manipulation
- 🔊 Web Audio API – for alarm sound on completion

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```bash
📁 countdown-timer-app/
├── index.html        # Markup and structure
├── styles.css        # All UI styling, layout, and responsiveness
├── script.js         # Core timer logic and interactivity
├── README.md         # Project documentation
└── /screenshots      # Screenshots for the README


## 🚀 🛠 How to Use
1. Clone the Repository
    git clone https://github.com/AkashKumar2011/JS-countDownTimer.git
    cd JS-countDownTimer

2. Open `index.html` in your web browser.
3. Click on "Add Timer" to create a new countdown timer.

